#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:453
msgid "What is a Distance Calculator?"
msgstr "Was ist ein Entfernungsrechner?"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:455
msgid ""
"A distance calculator computes the distance between two points in various "
"coordinate systems and using different distance metrics. It supports 2D and "
"3D Euclidean distance, Manhattan distance, geographic distance, and "
"Minkowski distance."
msgstr ""
"Ein Entfernungsrechner berechnet die Entfernung zwischen zwei Punkten in "
"verschiedenen Koordinatensystemen und unter Verwendung unterschiedlicher "
"Entfernungsmetriken. Es unterstützt 2D- und 3D-Euklidische Distanz, "
"Manhattan-Distanz, geografische Distanz und Minkowski-Distanz."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:463
msgid "Select the distance type from the dropdown menu"
msgstr "Wählen Sie den Entfernungstyp aus dem Dropdown-Menü aus"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:464
msgid ""
"Enter the coordinates for point 1 and point 2 based on the selected type"
msgstr ""
"Geben Sie die Koordinaten für Punkt 1 und Punkt 2 basierend auf dem "
"ausgewählten Typ ein"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:465
msgid "For geographic distance, enter latitude and longitude in degrees"
msgstr ""
"Geben Sie für die geografische Entfernung den Breiten- und Längengrad in "
"Grad ein"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:466
msgid ""
"For Minkowski distance, enter comma-separated coordinates and the p value"
msgstr ""
"Geben Sie für den Minkowski-Abstand durch Kommas getrennte Koordinaten und "
"den p-Wert ein"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:467
msgid "Click Calculate to get the distance with step-by-step solution"
msgstr ""
"Klicken Sie auf Berechnen, um die Entfernung mit einer Schritt-für-Schritt-"
"Lösung zu erhalten"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:468
msgid "Review the results, visualization, and detailed explanation"
msgstr ""
"Überprüfen Sie die Ergebnisse, die Visualisierung und die detaillierte "
"Erklärung"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:474
msgid "Understanding Distance Types"
msgstr "Distanztypen verstehen"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:477
msgid "Euclidean Distance"
msgstr "Euklidischer Abstand"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:479
msgid ""
"The straight-line distance between two points. In 2D: √((x₂-x₁)² + (y₂-"
"y₁)²). Represents the shortest path."
msgstr ""
"Der geradlinige Abstand zwischen zwei Punkten. In 2D: √((x₂-x₁)² + (y₂-"
"y₁)²). Stellt den kürzesten Weg dar."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:483
#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:738
msgid "Manhattan Distance"
msgstr "Manhattan-Entfernung"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:485
msgid ""
"The sum of absolute differences: |x₂-x₁| + |y₂-y₁|. Also called taxicab "
"distance, representing distance along grid lines."
msgstr ""
"Die Summe der absoluten Differenzen: |x₂-x₁| + |y₂-y₁|. Wird auch als "
"Taxientfernung bezeichnet und stellt die Entfernung entlang der Gitterlinien"
" dar."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:489
msgid "Geographic Distance"
msgstr "Geografische Entfernung"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:491
msgid ""
"Uses the Haversine formula to calculate great-circle distance between two "
"points on Earth using latitude and longitude."
msgstr ""
"Verwendet die Haversine-Formel, um die Großkreisentfernung zwischen zwei "
"Punkten auf der Erde anhand von Breiten- und Längengraden zu berechnen."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:497
msgid ""
"A generalized distance metric. p=1 gives Manhattan, p=2 gives Euclidean, p=∞"
" gives Chebyshev distance."
msgstr ""
"Eine verallgemeinerte Distanzmetrik. p=1 gibt Manhattan an, p=2 gibt den "
"euklidischen Abstand an, p=∞ gibt den Tschebyscheff-Abstand an."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:508
msgid "Example 1: 2D Euclidean Distance"
msgstr "Beispiel 1: 2D-euklidischer Abstand"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:509
msgid "Point 1: (0, 0), Point 2: (3, 4)"
msgstr "Punkt 1: (0, 0), Punkt 2: (3, 4)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:510
msgid "Distance: 5.0"
msgstr "Distanz: 5,0"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:513
msgid "Example 2: Geographic Distance"
msgstr "Beispiel 2: Geografische Entfernung"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:514
msgid "New York: (40.7128°N, 74.0060°W), London: (51.5074°N, 0.1278°W)"
msgstr "New York: (40,7128°N, 74,0060°W), London: (51,5074°N, 0,1278°W)"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:515
msgid "Distance: ~5,585 km"
msgstr "Entfernung: ~5.585 km"

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:528
msgid ""
"For geographic distance, latitude must be between -90° and 90°, longitude "
"between -180° and 180°."
msgstr ""
"Für die geografische Entfernung muss der Breitengrad zwischen -90° und 90° "
"und der Längengrad zwischen -180° und 180° liegen."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:534
msgid ""
"For Minkowski distance, both points must have the same number of dimensions."
msgstr ""
"Für den Minkowski-Abstand müssen beide Punkte die gleiche Anzahl an "
"Dimensionen haben."

#: Math_Calculators/templates/math_calculators/distance_calculator.html:540
msgid ""
"Euclidean distance is always less than or equal to Manhattan distance for "
"the same points."
msgstr ""
"Die euklidische Distanz ist für dieselben Punkte immer kleiner oder gleich "
"der Manhattan-Distanz."

